    <abstract>
      <t>This document describes the usage of Locator/ID Separation Protocol
   (LISP) as a solution to implement Computing-Aware Traffic Steering
   (CATS).  How LISP meets CATS requirements and how it fits to the
   control plane and data plane of CATS framework are presented.</t>
